He described another incident in which he was inappropriately touched in sight of other staff and students in the playground, saying: 'It was so common I wasn't sure it was wrong for teachers to touch me like that.' 

In 2009, Stewart was convicted of five counts of indecent assault and two counts of sexual assault. He was given a suspended sentence. 

Five former teachers have been convicted of sexual assault, however the inquiry has heard allegations against a further three staff members who have never been charged. 

